  "prompt": "If a contact has blocked me on their iPhone, and then they later decide to unblock me, will they then receive the messages I have sent to them?",
  "response": "When someone blocks you on their iPhone, any messages you send do not get delivered to them. If they later unblock you, those previously sent messages will not be delivered. Unblocking does not retroactively deliver messages that were sent while you were blocked. If you want them to see those messages, you would need to resend them after being unblocked.",
